name: Lorraine Lee Hammond
comments: Renowned Appalachian ducimer player, folksinger, songwriter and multi-instrumentalist, including banjo and mandolin.  Born in Connecticut and resides in Brookline, Massachussetts.  She is also a teacher of music.  Hammond is the former spouse of Rick Lee, with whom she recorded.  They were divorced in the 1980s.  She is now married to Bennett Hammond, a guitar player, with whom she performs.  Her maiden name is Choinere.

name: Al Sears
comments: Jazz and R&B saxophonist, manager and music publisher from Illinois. He played with Fats Waller, Chick Webb, Harry James, Lionel Hampton, Duke Ellington and Johnny Hodges. While with Hodges' band he wrote "Castle Rock" which became a big hit for Hodges. Subsequently, he recorded under his own name and became well known as a rock 'n' roll sax player and band leader. He worked closely with Alan Freed during this period.
